The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically named entity recognition (NER), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed approach involves using a translation system and a pre-trained high-resource language NER model, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions enriching semantic representations, which could involve neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
